    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>AI in Development</h2>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>Possibilities</h3>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üß™</span>
            Test Generation
          </h3>
          <p>Generating Unit, Integration and E2E tests</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üëÅÔ∏è</span>
            Code Reviews
          </h3>
          <p>Acceptance Criteria, Performance, Guidelines</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">‚ö°</span>
            Code Generation
          </h3>
          <p>Code generation at all levels</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">‚ú®</span>
            And more...
          </h3>
          <p>Documentation, refactoring, bug fixes</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; align-items: start;">
        <div>
          <h3>The Hype</h3>
          <ul style="list-style: none;">
            <li>‚ùå AI builds features autonomously</li>
            <li>‚ùå AI replaces developers</li>
            <li>‚ùå 10x productivity overnight</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="fragment">
          <h3>Reality</h3>
          <ul style="list-style: none;">
            <li>‚úÖ AI helps <strong>YOU</strong> building features</li>
            <li>‚úÖ AI empowers software engineers</li>
            <li>‚úÖ >2x productivity with proper setup</li>
            <li>‚úÖ >0x if used wrong</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>The "Junior Developer" Mental Model</h2>
      <p>Think of AI as a talented junior developer on your team.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; margin-top: 2rem; align-items: start;">
        
        <div>
          <h3>Junior devs need:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Good examples to follow</li>
            <li>Clear boundaries</li>
            <li>Code review</li>
            <li>Specific tasks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>AI needs the same:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Strong codebase patterns</li>
            <li>Well-defined scope</li>
            <li>Your oversight</li>
            <li>Focused objectives</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>What can go wrong?</h2>
      <h3>Why integrations fail?</h3>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <div style="border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üå™Ô∏è</span>
            Integrating AI everywhere at once
          </h3>
          <p><strong>Why it fails:</strong> No baseline to measure success, overwhelming to maintain</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">ü§ñ</span>
            Generating guidelines with AI
          </h3>
          <p><strong>Why it fails:</strong> AI doesn't understand your context deeply enough</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üèóÔ∏è</span>
            Big refactoring tasks
          </h3>
          <p><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Too much context, too many decisions, high risk</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.1);">
          <h3 style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üéØ</span>
            Feature one-shot generation
          </h3>
          <p><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Features need iteration, edge cases, business context</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.15);">
        <p style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 0;">
          <span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
          <strong>The Pattern: Lack of Foundation</strong> ‚Äî All of these fail because they skip the foundational work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>Building the Foundation</h2>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>1. Your Workflow Comes First</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Map your existing development workflow</li>
        <li>Identify pain points and high-value targets</li>
        <li>Only then consider where AI fits</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>2. Your Codebase = Training Data</h3>
      <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 2rem;">AI is pattern-matching, not magic</p>
      <div class="fragment">
        <p style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 2rem 0;">
          Garbage In ‚áí Garbage Out
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #a0aec0;">
          Your codebase quality directly determines AI output quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">3. The 3-Layer Approach</h3>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
        <div style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Most Important</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 1: Codebase</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Consistency and good examples</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Existing handlers show the pattern</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Supplements</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 2: Guidelines</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Navigates, restricts, clarifies</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Use error middleware, validate with Zod</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Quality Check</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 3: References</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Gold standard examples</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Point to best handler as reference</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</PresentationLayout>
